{
  "stem": "2996.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "His son, my grandfather, my mother's father, my grandfather married a Hungarian immigrant girl who was also a descendant of the same Maharam Shik-- see the relationship before they got married.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That Hungarian wife-- Hungarian-born wife-- went to Hungary with her three children-- my mother among them, the oldest-- to meet the relatives, the mishpocha.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On the way back, my grandmother died on the ship.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So there are three children arriving in Chicago-- or maybe my grandfather met them in new York.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That I don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Brought them to Chicago and didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Some people gave him advice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Go back and marry the sister.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Blood is being thicker than water, you know, that line.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he married her sister, brought her with him and the children back to Chicago.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she was not happy in America.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It wasn't kosher enough.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "No matter what, even if it says kosher outside of the butcher's shop, it's not kosher.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And later on, I found out in my life that that is correct.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Most of the so-called Jewish butchers are not kosher.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she did not give him peace until he found a way to go back to Europe and earn a livelihood.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he went to Vienna.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that's where my mother grew up, in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's how it happened that I was born in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was the last one to be born in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My kid brother was born in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you also told me on Monday that your father wanted you all to-- your parents wanted you to come back to the United States.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, one thing-- my grandfather was very, very patriotic American in the finest sense, not the ugly sense of the phony patriots.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
